node.text:
Fresh batch of Maximum Delight! Maximum Delight is an exceptionally aromatic and juicy dual-hop DIPA featuring Citra and Idaho 7. Tropicana™️ and Wrigley’s Juicy Fruit gum lead in aroma, but a secondary whiff delivers the dank green intensity of Idaho 7. Yellow stone fruit, mango, and resin on the palate. Delightful! 8% ABV — $20/4-pk.

Maximum Delight releases today from our taproom! We’re open from 2-10pm, with indoor seating beginning at 5.

node.text:
Bubble Massage! Our latest IPA—hopped with Centennial, El Dorado & Cashmere—is a late summer crusher that marries notes of bright tropical and citrus fruits with early autumn forest floor. Aromas of candied orange, melon, lemon verbena and POG juice lead to flavors of whole grapefruit, pineapple and pine sap. Medium bodied with a soft lingering bitterness. 6.6% ABV—$18/4-pk

Bubble Massage releases today! We’re open from 2-10pm with indoor bar service starting at 5pm!

node.text:
The ultimate poolside cooler! Spotlighting Galaxy and Motueka hops, Splish begins with a huge aroma of sweet mango. On the palate, we get waves of tropical fruit, lime zest, fresh squeezed OJ, and lime sherbet. Flaked oats in the grist give an extra creamy body. An absolute delight every time this beer comes around. Guest can art by @alfredstudio! 8% ABV — $20/4-pack⁣

Splish releases today! It will be available for shipping tomorrow. We’re open from 2-10pm with indoor service starting at 5pm.

node.text:
🍇🍑 Harvest continues! We’re looking forward to this year’s batch of Gathering Red Currants and Peaches — our GABF-medal-winning barrel aged sour ale conditioned on local currants and peaches. Our “gathering season” is possibly the most exciting time of the year for us. Sourcing whole, local fruit and allowing it to ferment spontaneously on its own gives us a special opportunity to connect with our regional terroir. Though this beer won’t be ready for some time, we couldn’t resist sharing a teaser of what’s to come.

—

Our taproom is open today from 2-10, with indoor seating beginning at 5.

node.text:
Introducing Frolic, our newest saison with brettanomyces & @indiehops experimental hop IH033. Aromas of traditional Belgian esters are interlaced with Brett and hop-driven savory floral funk. Flavors of biscuits with wildflower honey are complemented by a round, soft mouthfeel and slight bitter finish. A bright, funky & quaffable summertime saison! 5% ABV—$7/500ml

Frolic releases today! We are open from 2-10pm with indoor bar service starting at 5!

node.text:
Fresh batch of Invisible Touch! This unfiltered Helles-style lager, brewed using a double decoction mash, is a smooth, touch of sweet beaut. This batch uses Weyermann’s Barke Pilsner malt, our first time using this malt! We’re getting notes of honey and crisp biscuits, with a light mouthfeel and a soft but dry finish. 4.9% ABV — $17/4-pk.

Invisible Touch releases today! It will be available for shipping tomorrow. We’re open from 2-10pm with indoor bar service starting at 5pm!
